education-atlas
===============

A data-grounded map of educational problems by country and level, measured
against the UN Sustainable Development Goal 4 (Quality Education) framework.

Author:    Gianangelo Dichio
Publisher: bucket-foundation (https://bucket.foundation)
License:   MIT (code) / CC-BY-4.0 (published datasets)

This is Bucket Foundation's founding research: grounding the mission to reform
education in authoritative, traceable evidence rather than opinion.

Data sources retain their own terms. education-atlas stores provenance
(source, source_id, source_url, as_of) on every observation so each fact is
attributable to its origin. Source attributions:

  - World Bank EdStats         -- The World Bank (CC-BY-4.0)
                                  https://data.worldbank.org
  - UNESCO Institute for       -- UNESCO UIS (terms per uis.unesco.org)
    Statistics (UIS)              https://uis.unesco.org
  - Our World in Data          -- OWID (CC-BY-4.0; republishes cited sources)
                                  https://ourworldindata.org
  - OECD PISA 2022 Results     -- OECD (PISA 2022, Volume I)
                                  https://www.oecd.org/pisa

The framework (problem categories and benchmarks) follows UN SDG 4 targets and
the Education 2030 / Incheon Framework for Action. Benchmark provenance is
documented per indicator in edu/indicators.py.

Published datasets are intended to become citable Bucket Foundation canon
artifacts for the education-reform vertical.
